# Testing Conventions

This rule is auto-attached when test files are open or referenced.

## Standards

- Write tests that document intent, not implementation details
- Prefer descriptive test names that read as plain English
- Each test should cover one logical behavior
- Avoid testing private implementation details; test public interfaces
- Use test fixtures and factories instead of hardcoded data

